{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621162"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:50:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:50:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16675"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16675"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9366"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66262"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9366","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9366"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51711"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5338"},{"type":"tags","id":"5519"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22165"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22167"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66262","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66262"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPublic health interventions often focus on environmental modifications to protect population health. Traffic control measures are one example of structural interventions that can impact multiple health outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes how traffic control measures primarily contribute to population health?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reduces air pollution exposure","Promotes active transport usage","Decreases noise pollution levels","Reduces road traffic injuries and deaths","Improves social connectivity"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary public health benefit of traffic control measures is the \u003Cstrong\u003Ereduction of road traffic injuries and deaths\u003C/strong\u003E. This is achieved through speed limits, traffic signals, pedestrian crossings, and other infrastructure that prevents collisions between vehicles and pedestrians.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile traffic control measures have multiple benefits, the following are secondary outcomes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduction of air pollution exposure\u003C/strong\u003E occurs through improved traffic flow and reduced congestion, but this is not the main purpose of traffic control. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotion of active transport usage\u003C/strong\u003E through dedicated cycling and walking infrastructure is important but secondary to safety. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased noise pollution levels\u003C/strong\u003E result from better traffic management but are not the primary goal of traffic control measures. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImproved social connectivity\u003C/strong\u003E may occur through creation of pedestrian-friendly environments but is an indirect benefit. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional public health benefits of traffic control include reduced air pollution through congestion management, decreased noise pollution, and promotion of active transport through dedicated cycling and walking infrastructure. These factors contribute to reducing chronic disease burden in populations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Traffic control measures like speed limits and traffic signals reduce road traffic injuries and deaths through prevention of collisions.","Traffic control contributes to public health by reducing air pollution and noise pollution in urban areas.","Active transport infrastructure promotes physical activity and reduces chronic disease burden in populations."],"references":["Azami-Aghdash S, Gorji HA, Gharaee H, Moosavi A, Sadeghi-Bazargani H. Role of Health Sector in Road Traffic Injuries Prevention: A Public Health Approach. Int J Prev Med. 26;12:150. doi: 10.4103/ijpvm.IJPVM_225_19. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8631116/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51711"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16675"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51711"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-29T15:56:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T17:27:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9366"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66262"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","positi